aphorization of the EU as a »Global Player« and its ideological content, which portrays Europe as a neoliberal and masculine project.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aPolitical science (General). 4aDiskursanalyse. 4aEuropa. 4aEuropäische Politik. 4aIdeologiekritik. 4aIntersektionalität. 4aMaskulinismus. 4aMetapher. 4aMetaphernanalyse. 4aNeoliberalismus. 4aPolitik. 4aPolitikwissenschaft. 4aPolitische Theorie. 4aWissenssoziologie. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh  aCritique of Ideology.  aDiscourse Analysis.  aEurope.  aEuropean Politics.  aIntersectionality.  aMasculinism.  aMetaphor Analysis.  aMetaphor.  aNeoliberalism.  aPolitical Science.  aPolitical Theory.  aPolitics.  aSociology of Knowledge.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2015 Part 2z978311076664608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z97831107009850 cprintz978383763115940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839431153?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839431153zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839431153/original  a978-3-11-070098-5 DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  a978-3-11-076664-6 DG Plus PP Package 2015 Part 2b2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA